AVIAN INFLUENZA (247): AFRICA (NIGER) POULTRY, HPAI H5N1, WOAH
**************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 27 Dec 2022
Source: OIE-WAHIS (World Animal Health Information System) 2022 [edited]
https://wahis.woah.org/#/in-review/4802


Niger - Highly pathogenic avian influenza viruses (poultry)
-----------------------------------------------------------
Report type: immediate notification
Started: 14 Dec 2022
Confirmed: 17 Dec 2022
Reported: 26 Dec 2022
Reason for notification: recurrence
Last occurrence: 15 Jul 2022
Causal agent: highly pathogenic avian influenza virus [HPAI]
Serotype: H5N1
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

Outbreak location: Alloumoudou/Karofan, Bouza, Tahoua
Started: 14 Dec 2022
Epidemiological unit: village
Animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Birds / 4920 / 4870 / 4470 / 450 / 0 / 0
Affected population: poultry coming from the region of Zinder ordered by a local NGO

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: illegal movement of animals

Control measures at event level
Domestic animal control measures applied: control of wildlife reservoirs, zoning, traceability, surveillance outside the restricted zone, quarantine, disinfection, official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste
Wild animal control measures applied: control of wildlife reservoirs

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Outbreaks / Test / Test date / Result
Laboratoire central de l'Elevage (LABOCEL) / birds / 1 / real-time polymerase chain reaction (real-time PCR) / 17 Dec 2022 / positive

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the WOAH report at the source URL above.

Please note that any discrepancies in event start, confirmation, and other dates in ProMED posts and the WOAH corresponding reports are the result of a technical problem already being addressed by WOAH. - Mod.CRD]

